    If you dont need any upgrades than stick with the shard and shield combo. That shard will outdmg the AP. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=152485">Tigerheart</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umrbone1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MrBone1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/8/02 1:10:45 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What weapon?</span><hr size=1> I disagree, the AP will FAR outdamage the shard.  It's over rated, way over rated.  I'd go AP, sell shard and shield, and buy a nice haste item or what ever you need as another upgrade that will benefit you the most. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufolokthedwarf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Folok the Dwarf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/8/02 6:42:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.magelo.com/res/eq/itemicon/0247.png WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What weapon?</span><hr size=1> mds sux, i hated it so much. It does pos dmg. Sure ac is nice, but you got armor of faith. <p><b>Folok Solot</b><BR>
<i>Dwarven Knight of Drinal</i><BR>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utigerheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tigerheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/8/02 6:56:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What weapon?</span><hr size=1>     Can someone enlighten me plz. MDS does 19.00 Dmg per Sec. dmg bonus 11 at lvl 60. AP does 17.35 Dmg per sec with a 40 dmg bonus at 60. Does the AP really outdmg the MDS even though the MDS has a much higher DPS rating?? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=152485">Tigerheart</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urick7475.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rick7475</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/8/02 7:53:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Curious</span><hr size=1> I have observed the same thing about the DPS rating. And people have told me to stick with the MDS.<br>
<br>
The advantages I see with the MDS is that you get to bash with a shield, that adds a little more dmg, plus interrupts casters.<br>
<br>
Also if you proc dmg from spells, you get more of a chance to proc.<br>
<br>
I see a lot of 55+ pallies going with this weapon, and rarely see any weilding the AP. But I will see if I can pick up an AP to compare the two.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uenadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Enadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www-und.ida.liu.se/~tomsa548/EQ/sweden.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/9/02 6:10:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curious</span><hr size=1> I tried using <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/luthairsite/weaponCalc.html">Luthair's EQ Damage Calculator</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> for fun, and get:<br>
<br>
MDS = 885 DPM (24/30 11 bonus, bash damage not included)<br>
AP = 1209 DPM (42/49 42 bonus)<br>
<br>
So, according to the damage calculator, the AP have almost 37% higher damage output than the MDS. This is however without the added damage from bashes when using the MDS. Approximately how much damage does bash add at lvl 60? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urick7475.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rick7475</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/9/02 7:22:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curious</span><hr size=1> I used the calculator as well, and this is what I cam e up with, including some fudge factors.<br>
<br>
No haste was included in these calculations.<br>
<br>
Str at 165 (AP's strength can be offset with a shield str, so I averaged out the str to 165, which I used as an average pally stregth from a study of 25 pallies from level 50 to level 60 on Stormhammer).<br>
<br>
Shield bash is an extra 40 points (aprox 6-10 points per bash at about 6 bashes a minute, this may be disputed, but this is what I came up with).<br>
<br>
Weapon procs such as Divine Might (IoN is more, but I will assume we are not fighting undead for now) at 65dd for me happen on average of about 2-3 times a minute using MDS with an average of 60. I will fudge 1/3 less for AP cause of the delay, so MDS gets 2 procs, and AP gets one proc.<br>
<br>
MDS stats, BTW, are 28 30, not 24 30.<br>
<br>
Damage from the calculator for MDS is as follws:<br>
<br>
MDS 28 30, dmg bonus 11: 990 DPM<br>
Add shield bash: 990 + 40 = 1030.<br>
Add weap proc: 1030 + 120 = 1150.<br>
Total: 1150 DPM using MDS. (plus or minus a proc :) )<br>
<br>
AP 42 49, dmg bonus 42: 1193 DPM<br>
Add weap proc: 1193 + 60 = 1253 DPM. (plus or minus a proc)<br>
<br>
Against undead with IoN, add 500 to MDS for 1650 DPM and add 250 to AP for 1503. So against undead, MDS may be better than AP.<br>
<br>
Calculations and fudge factors are mine :)<br>
<br>
<br>
I also did a comparison with the warrior's epic, Blade of Tactics and Blade of strategy.<br>
<br>
Blade of Strategy procs a 100pt hp drain, so I gave it 3 procs per minute.<br>
<br>
Buffs and other procs are not included, as pallies have similiar buffs, and str again was at 165, though it may be higher for barbs, trolls, etc. <br>
<br>
I also gave 40points to warrior kicks, assuming 6 kicks a minute (talking to a friend said that was about right)<br>
<br>
Blade of Tactic primary, 14 24, dmg bonus 9 <br>
Blade of Strategy secondary, 14 24, no dmg bonus.<br>
1014 DPM.<br>
Add procs of about 300 for 1314 DPM.<br>
Add kicks of about 40 for 1344 DPM.<br>
<br>
<br>
So, IMHO, pally and warrior dmg is pretty close. But when fighting undead, it is obvious pallies rule and the MDS is the best of these weapons. Heck, fighting undead last night, my MDS proced 4 times in a row, for 1k worth of dmg, bringing it to 2200 DPM :)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Rick



</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urick7475.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rick7475</A> at: 4/9/02 7:38:45 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubizomb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bizomb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Fatcat </span><br>  Posts: 957<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/9/02 8:25:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Curious</span><hr size=1> Using an L55 paladin with 150 str and 0 haste for simplicity.<br>
<br>
AP 42/49 DB of 42.<br>
1187 damage. <br>
<br>
MDS 28/30 DB of 11.<br>
982 damage.<br>
<br>
This is about right. The damage bonus is what kills the MDS. It's a very slow delay 1 hander so you are losing serious damage due to the crappy DB.<br>
<br>
So you can see that AP is half the cost of MDS and it puts out 20% more damage.<br>
I would suggest dumping MDS and going the 2 hander route. Save up the extra plat and buy an RBG or something.<br>
<br>
Biz. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=430.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=430.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=430.topic&index=8><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=430.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.threadControl?topicID=430.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=430.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=430.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="paladinsofnorrathgeneral">General<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm14">Norrath Classic and Kunark<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm15">Velious and Luclin<option value="paladinsofnorrathholyswordsandquests">Quests Forum<option value="paladinsofnorrathfrm12">Equip